                better performance, consider increasing the memory. The total memory available to
                the node must be distributed between the host operating system, the Elasticsearch
                java heap space, and the kernel file system caches. For example, if the system has
                32 GB memory, 2 GB must be allocated for the host operating system, 15 GB for the
                java heap space, and the remaining 15 GB for the file system caches. </p>
